
[1]mechanically

   MECHAN'ICALLY, adv. According to the laws of mechanism, or good
   workmanship.

   1. By physical force or power.

   2. By the laws of motion, without intelligence or design, or by the
   force of habit. We say, a man arrives to such perfection in playing on
   an instrument, that his fingers move mechanically.

    Mechanically turned or inclined, naturally or habitually disposed to
                            use mechanical arts.
